# Normalize line endings for files whose byte-exact contents are
# compared by tests. Snapshot fixtures must stay LF on every host so
# `include_str!` produces identical bytes across Windows, macOS, and
# Linux checkouts.
*.snap text eol=lf

# Vendored Solidity sources whose byte-exact contents are compared by
# `parity-maintainer verify-sol-provenance` against the upstream pins in
# `parity/source-lock.yaml`. Any host that re-normalises CRLF on checkout
# would break the SHA-256 gate; force LF on every host so the
# bytes-on-disk SHA matches the git-blob SHA matches the upstream SHA.
crates/contracts/abi/**/*.sol text eol=lf

# YAML files under parity/openapi/ are byte-compared by Rust tooling:
# `parity/openapi/services-orderbook.yml` is a vendored upstream
# snapshot whose four-line "Vendored from cowprotocol/services @
# <commit>" header pins it to a specific upstream commit, and the
# `*-inventory.yaml` plus `coverage.yaml` manifests are read by the
# DTO coverage validator. CRLF on any host would change the bytes
# under both contracts.
parity/openapi/**/*.yaml text eol=lf
parity/openapi/**/*.yml text eol=lf

# Frozen wire-byte fixtures pinned by Rust regression tests through
# `include_str!`. CRLF would corrupt the byte-equality assertion the
# fixture is built to enforce.
parity/fixtures/**/*.json text eol=lf

# Source-lock manifests carry pinned upstream commit hashes and are
# parsed by `cargo parity-validate`. LF normalisation keeps the parser
# input identical across hosts.
parity/source-lock.yaml text eol=lf

# COW Shed proxy creation-code is RAW EVM bytecode, not text. Mark it
# explicitly `binary` so git neither normalises nor diffs the byte
# stream. The neighbouring `.sha256` digest files ARE text and stay
# LF-normalised so `build.rs::validate_cow_shed_proxy_artifacts`
# sees the same digest bytes on every host.
crates/contracts/abi/cow-shed/proxy-creation-code/*.bin binary
crates/contracts/abi/cow-shed/proxy-creation-code/*.sha256 text eol=lf
